Lagos – Following his alleged rating for the 2018 Confederation of African Football (CAF) Player of the Year award, ex-international, Taiwo Oloyede has tipped Ahmed Musa to win the trophy. SUNDAY INDEPENDENT learnt that the trio of Musa, William Troost-Ekong, and Oghenekaro Etebo are highly rated for nominations. According to feelers, the players will be named among the nominees when the shortlist for the awards rolls out next month and Oloyede is sticking his neck out for Musa. “I also got the information and I want to believe that Musa stands a good chance of winning the award irrespective of nominations from other countries. “He had a good outing at the 2018 FIFA World Cup in Russia and has been making waves in his new club, Al Nassr in Saudi Arabia. “All these and other considerations put together will give him an edge at the end of the voting”, said Oloyede. Musa, on Wednesday announced his arrival in the Saudi Arabian league after scoring hat trick for his new club Al Nassr.  Musa joined the Saudi Arabian from Leicester City FC in August in a deal worth £17.5 million. The deal reportedly makes him the highest paid Nigerian football player. It will be recalled that CAF President, Ahmad Ahmad has affirmed that the 2018 CAF awards will take place in Dakar, Senegal on January 8, 2019 in collaboration with Senegalese authorities. Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 